SINGAPORE DAYBOOK: Allgreen Offer, Capital Markets Forum

-- B y   L a r s   K l e m m i n g   a n d   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 
2011-05-23T22:09:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/singapore-daybook-allgreen-offer-capital-markets-forum.html
Malaysian billionaire  Robert Kuok 
offered to buy all the shares in Allgreen Properties Ltd.
through an investment holding firm, valuing the developer at
S$2.54 billion ($2 billion).  WHAT TO WATCH:  *Allgreen Properties Ltd. (AG SP) said it received a takeover
offer from Malaysian billionaire Robert Kuok of S$1.60 a share
versus last traded price of S$1.15. Kuok group companies already
hold 55.7% of the shares.
*Bukit Sembawang Estates Ltd. (BS SP) said 4Q net income fell 34%
to S$27.5m.
*Keppel Corp. (KEP SP) said a unit won an order from Vision
Drilling Pte. to build a jackup drilling rig for $180 million.
*Kreuz Holdings Ltd. (KRZ SP) said it won contracts worth $44m.
*Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL SP) approached banks seeking $2.25
billion of revolving credit facilities, according to a person
familiar with the matter. The facility will pay a so-called
blended margin of 162 bps more than Libor, the person said.
*Nordic Group Ltd. (NRD SP) said it is seeking approval from
shareholders to buy Multiheight Group for up to S$47m.
*Silverlake Axis Ltd. (SILV SP) said it won a contract from
Thanachart Bank.
*Stamford Tyres Corp. (STC SP) said it bought the remaining 50%
of STC Tyres ( Malaysia ).
*Swiber Holdings Ltd. said it won contracts worth $109m for oil
projects in  Asia .
*Unionmet Singapore Ltd. (UMS SP) said it sold its stake in
Guangxi Crystal Union Photoelectric Materials Co.  CONFERENCES:  *Euromoney Australian and  New Zealand  Debt Capital Markets Forum
2011 held at Singapore Marriott Hotel. Speakers include New
Zealandâ€™s Finance Minister Bill English.  MARKETS:  S&P 500  down 1.2% to 1,317.37
Stoxx Europe 600 down 1.7% to 274.78
MSCI Asia Pacific down 2.2% to 131.60
Straits Times Index down 1.8% to 3,110.48  BTV:  7:10 a.m.: AMP Capital Head of Investment Strategy Shane Oliver
